If you love to sleep all the time, you will become poor;
\q2 stay awake when you should be at work and you will have plenty to eat. 
\q1

26:
A king who is wise will separate the wicked from among his people;
\q2 then he will drive a threshing cart over their bodies to kill them. 
\q1

28:
Love and faithfulness preserve the life of the king; 
\q2 his throne is made strong by steadfast love. 
